title: Date of the contract
explanation: The text states 'dated as of July 12, 2017', which is the standard way to indicate the contract date.

explanation: The text lists 'Cambridge Master Fund L.P.' as one of the parties and explicitly refers to it as 'Party B'.

title: Specified transaction scope
explanation: The text explicitly amends the definition of 'Specified Transaction' from Section 14 by inserting new language and exclusions, indicating a non-standard scope.

title: Cross default applicable parties
explanation: The text states that the Cross-Default provisions of Section 5(a)(vi) will apply, but does not specify only one party. In ISDA Schedules, unless specified otherwise, this typically means both parties (Party A and Party B) are subject to Cross Default.

title: Specified indebtness includes borrowed_money
explanation: The text does not mention whether borrowed money is included in Specified Indebtedness.

title: Specified indebtness excludes deposits
explanation: The text explicitly states that Specified Indebtedness shall exclude, in relation to Party A, any deposits received in the ordinary course of business.

title: amount for Party A
explanation: The threshold for Party A is defined as a percentage, not a fixed amount.

title: currency for Party A
explanation: No currency is specified for Party A, as the threshold is a percentage of shareholders' equity.

title: percentage for Party A
explanation: The text states 'an amount equal to 3 % of its total shareholders' equity' for Party A.

title: percentage reference for Party A

title: Party for calculation agent
explanation: The text states 'the Calculation Agent will be Party A; provided, however, that if an Event of Default occurs and is continuing in respect of Party A, the Calculation Agent will be Party B or an Independent Dealer...'. Therefore, Party A is the default Calculation Agent, with exceptions if Party A defaults.
